	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: HIROM game on a LOROM board ?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I have converted Lo rom boards into HI rom just by cutting some paths int the board and reconnecting them to another locations, see romlab to get the idea.<br /><br />I am currently working on a PCB design to use with 4 27c801 or 2 29F032 hi/lo rom with a lot of switches to control if there is normal pinout or bankswitched, if it is 1 memory or 2, .if they are hi or lo rom, etc. just to have it connected to a single lo rom PCB and it will act as a test board in any case scenario.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
